# Bash color

## Available colors

- BLACK
- RED
- GREEN
- BROWN
- BLUE
- PURPLE
- CYAN
- LIGHT_GRAY
- DEFAULT
- DARK_GRAY
- LIGHT_RED
- LIGHT_GREEN
- YELLOW
- LIGHT_BLUE
- LIGHT_PURPLE
- LIGHT_CYAN
- WHITE

## Available effect

- BOLD
- DIM (not working on Konsole)
- UNDERLINE
- BLINK (not working on Konsole and Gnome Terminal)
- INVERSE
- HIDDEN (not working on Konsole)

## Example

```python
from bashcolor import RED, UNDERLINE, colorize

print(colorize('Red color', RED))
print(colorize('Red background', background=RED))
print(colorize('Underline', effects=[UNDERLINE]))
```

## API

```python
def colorize(
    text,
    color=None,
    background=None,
    effects=[],
    color_256=None,
    background_256=None,
    with_end=True):
```


